snippet.textDisplay: “Jhol is a story about a deep love ripped to shreds, of whispers and hearsay, of jealousy and sabotage, but also missed opportunities, the grief of loss, and of being entirely helpless in the face of forces beyond your control. The song speaks of love and loss, of separation, so I constructed the narrative out of that premise, writing characters based on classic archetypes from literary tragedies, and playing out in an alternative Pakistan where art, music, film, performance was encouraged and allowed to thrive.” – Jamal Rahman
